<author><name><![CDATA[MottZilla]]></name></author>
<updated>2009-04-02T14:27:17-07:00</updated>
<published>2009-04-02T12:17:02-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5002&amp;p=45071#p45071</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5002&amp;p=45071#p45071"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Need help making FF3j english translation cart please]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5002&amp;p=45071#p45071"><![CDATA[
FF3j uses a TNROM board. There are no US games that use TNROM. TNROM is up to 512k PRG, 8K PRGRAM with battery backup, and 8K CHRRAM. You can convert a TKROM board to TNROM by replacing the CHRROM chip with 8K CHRRAM. I believe this is how most if not all FF3j repros are made.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1726">MottZilla</a> — Thu Apr 02, 2009 12:17 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
