<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[AWal]]></name></author>
<updated>2009-03-31T14:54:10-07:00</updated>
<published>2009-03-31T14:54:10-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5002&amp;p=44992#p44992</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5002&amp;p=44992#p44992"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Need help making FF3j english translation cart please]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5002&amp;p=44992#p44992"><![CDATA[
Cajones, although dated and a console application, tends to do a good job splitting prg (and chr) when outputting to the "PasoFami" format (PRG and CHR split with an FRM).<br /><br />P.S.: The rule of thumb for repro compatibility is to make sure the board has sufficient size, in the case of FF2J, you need to find an SNROM cartridge with a 2Mbit game code...In the case of the US the only cart sufficient without aditional wires is Hillsfar AD&amp;D (ouch)...Unless you are willing to wire a Bomberman II (quite uncommon) or Kid Icarus (unnessecarily expensive).<br /><br />Not to discourage any advanced cartridges, but for a first repro, I would recommend just socketing an NROM cart. Easy, Simple, and you can see what could possibly go wrong.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=26">AWal</a> — Tue Mar 31, 2009 2:54 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
